parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including loss of headlights, horn malfunction, and anti-theft system problems, which can lead to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of headlights
and issues with the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of ignition
and issues with the ignition switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to become stranded, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete activation of the anti-theft system
and problems with the Passlock system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete loss of headlights
issues with the daytime running lights
and problems with the headlight relay.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission can cause loss of control, leading to safety risks and accidents.
symptoms: Slipping or hesitation of the transmission
and problems with the transmission solenoids.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Leaks in the intake manifold gaskets can cause engine performance issues, stalling, and overheating, leading to accidents or engine damage.
Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
Failure of the fuel pump can cause engine stalling, loss of power, and difficulty restarting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Electrical issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: electrical window and door lock issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-miss situations, especially on slippery or bumpy roads.
symptoms: the vehicle locks up or skids
and the "TRAC OFF" light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brakes fail to engage properly
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake components, such as calipers or brake shoes, can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle pulls to one side when braking.
